♪ Well, I had a friend
named Rambling Bob

14:15.333 --> 14:18.333
♪ He used to steal,
gamble and rob

14:18.400 --> 14:19.667
♪ He thought he was
the smartest guy in town ♪

14:19.733 --> 14:22.300
Cheer up, Sam!
We all gotta start somewhere!

14:23.600 --> 14:24.667
Yee-haw!

14:24.733 --> 14:27.467
♪ But I found out
last Monday

14:27.533 --> 14:30.433
♪ That Bob got
locked up Sunday

14:30.500 --> 14:36.167
♪ They took him to
the jailhouse way down town ♪

14:37.600 --> 14:38.633
Jack, man.

14:39.800 --> 14:41.800
I can't stay here.

14:41.867 --> 14:43.567
Everybody's going or gone.

14:44.600 --> 14:45.833
Memphis.

14:45.900 --> 14:47.633
Detroit.

14:47.700 --> 14:49.200
Any place except here.

14:51.233 --> 14:53.900
And now every night,
I gotta hear every which way

14:53.967 --> 14:57.500
about the coloreds
in the Murphy place.

14:57.567 --> 15:00.700
They could save daddy's
damn life and
he would still cuss 'em out.

15:05.233 --> 15:07.067
I'll come back
and visit with you.

15:11.067 --> 15:14.067
But right now I need to
see this place
in my rearview mirror.

15:30.733 --> 15:31.967
So?

15:32.067 --> 15:33.300
How do we sound?

15:34.733 --> 15:36.067
Let's take a listen.

15:55.567 --> 15:58.233
♪ ...ing cards
and shooting dice

15:58.300 --> 16:00.733
♪ He's in the jailhouse now

16:06.567 --> 16:08.167
What do you think,
Mr. Phillips?

16:08.233 --> 16:10.900
Ooh!
That's a good job, fellas.

16:10.967 --> 16:13.600
You'll make folks mighty glad
they got electricity!

16:13.667 --> 16:15.633
We'll have those 17 disks
ready for you tomorrow.

16:15.700 --> 16:19.767
So bring a check
for 68 dollars for the disks
and 11 for studio time.

16:19.833 --> 16:22.433
-Uh...
-That's 79.

16:22.500 --> 16:24.967
Make it out to
Memphis Recording Service.

16:25.067 --> 16:27.233
Yes, ma'am. I'm hauling' for
Light, Gas, and Water,

16:27.300 --> 16:29.200
so I'll be here just
as soon as I get off work.

16:29.833 --> 16:30.700
Thank you.

16:30.767 --> 16:33.333
Bye!

16:33.400 --> 16:36.500
All right,
sounded pretty good.

16:36.567 --> 16:38.300
It sounded to me like
right on the money, fellas!

16:38.367 --> 16:40.100
Yeah, I think
we really got something here.

16:40.167 --> 16:43.067
We did it! Our first session!

16:43.067 --> 16:47.067
Who would've thought I'd come
from Nashville to record
hillbilly music.

16:47.100 --> 16:49.233
Third-rate hillbilly music.

16:49.300 --> 16:51.400
Oh, you're too hard
on them, Sam.

16:51.467 --> 16:53.267
Don't worry, it gets better.

16:53.333 --> 16:56.667
-Hmm?
-You're recording a Catholic
funeral in Covington tomorrow!

