♪ You've drowned the Pharaoh
Oh, Mary, don't

18:35.300 --> 18:41.300
♪ I said, Mary tell Martha
not to mourn
Tell Martha not to mourn

18:41.367 --> 18:44.767
♪ To mourn!

18:52.233 --> 18:54.733
Listen to me,
brothers and sisters.

18:54.800 --> 18:57.867
Don't let the Devil rent
no space in your head.

19:00.133 --> 19:01.700
Now.

19:01.767 --> 19:07.067
God can see a black ant
on a black rock
on a black night.

19:07.067 --> 19:09.800
You can maybe slide
a little something
past your wife,

19:09.867 --> 19:12.700
your husband,
or even your boss,

19:12.767 --> 19:15.767
but you can't hide
nothing from God!

19:15.833 --> 19:16.967
Do you hear me?

19:17.067 --> 19:18.667
Now, think on that awhile,
won't you?

19:18.733 --> 19:22.733
You gotta tell the Devil
right here, right now,

19:22.800 --> 19:26.267
he ain't gonna rent no space
in your head.

19:26.333 --> 19:28.200
Can I get a amen?

19:28.267 --> 19:29.500
Yeah!

19:29.567 --> 19:31.600
Above the screaming
and crying of them

19:31.667 --> 19:36.333
that keeps putting off being
saved 'cause they say they got
more important business.

19:36.400 --> 19:38.067
Yeah!

19:38.067 --> 19:43.467
All the way down there,
I want the Devil to hear
you say, "Yeah!"

19:44.967 --> 19:46.600
Whoo!

19:46.667 --> 19:48.967
Remember, we are heading
for better days,

19:49.067 --> 19:52.733
when all men will walk
together as brothers.

19:52.800 --> 19:56.833
Come on, Brother Ernest
and lead us on
out with Run On!

20:03.833 --> 20:06.667
♪ You gonna run
on for a long time

20:06.733 --> 20:09.500
-* Run on for a long time
Yeah!

20:09.567 --> 20:12.500
-* Run on for a long time
-Come on, baby face!

20:12.567 --> 20:14.567
Raise your voice!
Let's hear you!

20:14.633 --> 20:17.200
♪ Run on for a long time

20:17.267 --> 20:19.033
♪ Run on for a long time

20:19.100 --> 20:22.133
-* You gonna run on
for a long time *
-Come on, come on!

20:22.200 --> 20:24.567
It's all right, come on!

20:24.633 --> 20:26.200
Come on! Yeah, that's it!

20:26.267 --> 20:27.933
That's it, baby! That's it!

20:28.000 --> 20:30.100
♪ My head's been wet
with the midnight dew

20:30.167 --> 20:32.400
♪ Coming down on bended knee

20:32.467 --> 20:35.000
♪ Talking about the man
from Galilee

20:35.067 --> 20:37.467
♪ My God spoke,
He spoke so sweet

20:37.533 --> 20:40.333
♪ I thought I heard
the shuffle of angel's feet ♪

20:40.400 --> 20:43.467
U.S. and UN troops
have gathered in Pusan.

20:43.533 --> 20:45.400
General Ridgeway says
after two years,

20:45.467 --> 20:48.400
the campaign against
the North Koreans is not to
seize ground,

20:48.467 --> 20:51.267
-but to halt the Communist...
-We've had about
enough of that.

20:51.333 --> 20:55.533
Well, if they just dropped
one of them nuclear bombs on
'em like we done to the Japs.

20:55.600 --> 20:57.467
Stop wasting American lives.

21:00.100 --> 21:04.667
J.R., why don't you help me
on I Got That Joy.

21:04.733 --> 21:06.400
Hmm? Let's lighten
the mood a little.

21:07.700 --> 21:10.200
Love hearing you sing.

21:10.267 --> 21:16.633
♪ I've got that joy, joy, joy,
joy down in my heart

21:16.700 --> 21:19.133
♪ Down in my heart

21:19.200 --> 21:21.133
♪ Down in my heart

21:21.200 --> 21:26.300
♪ I've got that joy, joy, joy,
joy down in my...
Down in my heart ♪

21:30.167 --> 21:31.567
What's got you so glum, J.R.?

21:40.233 --> 21:42.533
Daddy, Momma.

21:44.200 --> 21:47.533
Look, I know that
this probably
ain't the time, but...

21:48.667 --> 21:50.567
I went by
the enlistment center.

21:52.767 --> 21:55.367
Joined the Air Force.

21:55.433 --> 21:59.333
You are gonna get blown to
bits over there in that Korea.

21:59.400 --> 22:00.933
Nah, they gave me a choice.

22:01.700 --> 22:03.400
Alaska or Germany.

22:03.467 --> 22:06.233
Pretty sure I'm shipping out
to Germany
after basic training.

22:06.300 --> 22:08.167
Germany is so far away.

22:08.233 --> 22:10.467
Your ass'll be on the front
line if the Commies invade,
Johnny Boy.

22:10.533 --> 22:12.467
"The good Lord promises
us many things,

22:12.533 --> 22:14.733
"but He doesn't promise
us tomorrow."

22:15.567 --> 22:16.933
You know that, Daddy.

22:20.233 --> 22:23.267
This should've been
the Cash family farm.

22:23.333 --> 22:26.067
That's why I poured so much
sweat into clearing and all,
I cannot...

22:26.067 --> 22:28.233
Daddy, look,

22:28.300 --> 22:30.733
this land here doesn't make
but a bale an acre
in a good year

22:30.800 --> 22:33.333
and there ain't been
a good year in a while.

22:33.400 --> 22:36.800
'Tween the skitters
and the floods, it's just
low-rent, bottom land.

23:04.067 --> 23:06.100
I'm gonna miss all of you
every day.

23:07.800 --> 23:09.533
Good Lord knows I will.

23:10.700 --> 23:13.400
Your daddy loves you, John.

23:13.467 --> 23:16.533
He can't bear to lose
another son.

23:16.600 --> 23:20.233
I believe I might just
love him more from
6,000 miles away.

23:28.867 --> 23:31.533
♪ From the day I whisper

23:31.600 --> 23:34.833
Randall, I need to stop
at Piggly Wiggly, and get some
cornmeal for my fritters.

23:34.900 --> 23:36.567
And vanilla bean ice cream.

23:38.733 --> 23:40.167
That the Presley boy?

23:43.867 --> 23:46.067
Why is Elvis
at the colored church?

23:46.067 --> 23:48.533
I knew that Presley kid
was nothin' but trouble.

23:48.600 --> 23:50.933
I told you so.

23:51.067 --> 23:53.767
You will never see him again,
you hear me?

23:54.467 --> 23:55.967
Never!

23:56.067 --> 23:57.167
Never!

24:04.667 --> 24:06.133
Over there!

24:22.900 --> 24:25.167
Come on!
Gather round, gather round!

24:25.233 --> 24:26.500
Come on, folks!

24:26.567 --> 24:28.500
You seen grandma dance
when she's had a belt,

24:28.567 --> 24:31.400
but you ain't never seen
dancing ducks!

24:31.467 --> 24:33.067
No way, no how.

24:33.067 --> 24:35.067
Five cents will get you
somethin' you're gonna talk

24:35.100 --> 24:37.567
about for the rest
of your days!

24:37.633 --> 24:40.633
Now, Alabama ain't seen
nothin' like this.

24:40.700 --> 24:44.333
You shoot 'em, you eat 'em,
you chase 'em round the yard,

24:44.400 --> 24:48.133
you seen 'em floating'
in the pool, but you ain't
never seen 'em dance.

25:15.167 --> 25:18.133
There ain't no music
and them ducks
are still dancing.

25:18.200 --> 25:19.367
It's rigged!

25:19.433 --> 25:21.967
Uh, music or no music,
the ducks keep dancing.

25:22.067 --> 25:24.467
It's like the melodies
are in their head!

25:24.533 --> 25:25.767
It's amazing!

25:26.767 --> 25:28.367
There's no need for that now.

25:28.433 --> 25:30.300
Oh! I don't appreciate that.

25:31.833 --> 25:33.967
Madam, you are no lady.

25:34.067 --> 25:35.267
Where're you going?

25:39.067 --> 25:41.267
All right now, hold on!
Now, hold on!

25:41.333 --> 25:44.233
-Hold on!
-I want my money back!

25:44.300 --> 25:45.767
Hold on! Let me explain.

25:45.833 --> 25:47.600
That's just to keep 'em warm.
That's all.

25:47.667 --> 25:49.933
That's just...
It's chilly out!

25:50.067 --> 25:53.967
♪ Singing this cattle call

25:54.067 --> 25:55.967
Hey, it's Eddy!

25:56.067 --> 26:00.167
All right, all right,
everybody!

26:00.233 --> 26:02.767
That's Eddy Arnold, boy!
Go get his autograph!

26:03.967 --> 26:05.733
Hey, Eddy!
Come on!

26:19.333 --> 26:22.333
You saved the
Colonel's ass, son.

26:22.400 --> 26:26.167
Yeah, I've been wondering'
how you got all them
ducks to dance.

26:26.233 --> 26:28.900
And if it gets too hot,
I got dinner!

26:31.233 --> 26:34.767
You know, Colonel,
I just signed with RCA Victor.

26:34.833 --> 26:36.300
Sure could use
a good front man.

26:41.700 --> 26:43.900
I'd have to give up the ducks.

26:45.433 --> 26:46.767
Mmm-hmm.

26:46.833 --> 26:48.367
I tell you what,

26:48.433 --> 26:51.833
if the Colonel were
to be persuaded,

26:51.900 --> 26:55.733
when you drive into town,
you'll see your face
on every lamp post,

26:55.800 --> 26:58.233
hear every drunk
singing your song.

26:58.933 --> 27:00.433
Is that right?

27:00.500 --> 27:01.500
Uh-huh.

27:03.867 --> 27:05.533
That sounds like a deal.

27:05.600 --> 27:06.800
All right.

27:08.433 --> 27:10.367
Here's what
we're gonna do first.

27:14.433 --> 27:17.267
Boy, I tell you,
I'm in bad shape, boy!

27:18.400 --> 27:21.800
If you can't lay on her,
then, boy!

27:24.100 --> 27:26.367
Yeah, sir, good people,
it's Daddy O'Dewey,

27:26.433 --> 27:30.600
coming at you from
the Chisca Hotel, Red, Hot
and Blue 56 WHBQ.

27:30.667 --> 27:33.300
Hottest cotton picking thing
in the country, boy.

27:33.367 --> 27:34.900
Better believe it!

27:34.967 --> 27:38.067
Brought to you
here tonight by CV Beer.

27:38.100 --> 27:39.500
Champagne Velvet.

27:39.567 --> 27:41.500
This right here is the best
beer money can buy.

27:41.567 --> 27:43.833
Drink it now or,
hell, freeze it for later.

27:43.900 --> 27:46.833
Just make sure you always
got a case or two on hand.

27:46.900 --> 27:48.900
All right!

27:48.967 --> 27:52.400
Now, did they boost us to
50,000 watts yet, Diz?

27:52.467 --> 27:53.767
Not yet, partner.

27:53.833 --> 27:55.767
Well, gosh-darn,

27:55.833 --> 28:00.267
but you can hear us clear
across Arkansas if that
wind's blowing just right.

28:00.333 --> 28:03.400
Now, we gonna slow it down.

28:03.467 --> 28:06.100
If you wanna make a move
with your old lady,
well, now's the time.

28:06.167 --> 28:08.100
Let's go, old man!

28:12.700 --> 28:13.900
How's it going, cuz?

28:15.100 --> 28:16.600
Pills are hitting
good tonight, boy.

28:16.667 --> 28:18.167
I might be up till Tuesday.

28:18.233 --> 28:19.733
What, what day
is it today, cuz?

28:19.800 --> 28:21.900
-Sunday all day.
-Sunday. Bath day.

28:21.967 --> 28:23.333
Well, that's a good deal.

28:23.400 --> 28:26.233
So how's that, uh,
studio of yours shaping up?

28:26.300 --> 28:30.967
Well, to tell you the truth,
I'm recording piss-poor
hillbilly bands and funerals.

28:31.800 --> 28:33.067
Man!

28:34.967 --> 28:38.733
Now what makes a cat like
Mr. Sam Phillips here come
all the way to Memphis?

28:38.800 --> 28:40.833
I wanna make music, man.

28:40.900 --> 28:42.933
Man, Memphis got everything.

28:43.067 --> 28:46.267
Hillbilly, big old orchestras
at the Peabody, blues straight
up from the Delta.

28:46.333 --> 28:48.300
Dear, God!
You like our colored
Rhythm 'n' Blues!

28:48.367 --> 28:51.133
No, man, the way I see it,
music ain't got no color.

28:51.200 --> 28:53.100
You open your soul to it,
and it'll...

28:53.167 --> 28:56.400
It'll make you feel like
your walking down Beale Street
on a Saturday night.

28:56.467 --> 28:57.700
Exactly, man!

28:57.767 --> 28:59.500
Man, good music is gonna find
good people.

28:59.567 --> 29:02.633
Now, I believe that
in my heart and soul.

29:02.700 --> 29:05.067
I'll tell you
what I really wanna do, man.

29:05.067 --> 29:09.233
I wanna find me songs
that I can feed to one of them
big old record companies, huh?

29:09.300 --> 29:10.667
Well, I got me a song.

29:10.733 --> 29:12.267
Yeah, it's called
Get off the Turntable, Mable.

29:12.333 --> 29:14.933
You're Too Old to Be
Running Around.

29:15.067 --> 29:17.067
What do you think
of that there, Sam?

29:17.133 --> 29:20.500
Man, I think people are gonna
be stacked up clear 'cross
Arkansas to buy it, man.

29:22.167 --> 29:23.467
Friends and neighbors,
little rabbit twisters,

29:23.533 --> 29:25.133
we've been talking
with Mr. Sam Phillips.

29:25.200 --> 29:27.367
Memphis Recording Service.
Go on down, see Sam.

29:27.433 --> 29:29.700
Union Marshall.
Run a carload of mad hogs

29:29.767 --> 29:34.967
through the front door
and tell him, Phillips sent
you from Red, Hot and Blue!

29:35.533 --> 29:37.067
Whoo!

29:37.133 --> 29:40.100
You son of a...
Man, you should have told me
we was live.

29:40.167 --> 29:42.100
Man, I knew you wouldn't say
nothin' dirty.

29:42.167 --> 29:44.500
All right,
tell you what, Slick.

29:44.567 --> 29:47.233
Fella coming down here
next week from Los Angeles.

29:47.300 --> 29:49.167
Joe Bihari, Modern Records,
okay?

29:49.233 --> 29:51.200
So maybe I could
put you with him.

29:51.267 --> 29:55.367
He's all the time bitchin'
'bout having to record
in hotels and Elks Clubs.

29:56.467 --> 29:57.500
Bring him on.

29:58.533 --> 29:59.833
Bring him on, man.

29:59.900 --> 30:01.800
Yeah, he's cutting
a new fella I hipped him to.

30:01.867 --> 30:03.267
Guitar player.

30:03.333 --> 30:04.567
Whoa!

30:04.633 --> 30:07.967
He can play his black ass off,
man. B.B. King.

30:08.033 --> 30:09.967
Maybe you could
record him, hmm?

30:10.767 --> 30:12.100
I'd appreciate that.

30:13.933 --> 30:15.567
Dog gone, I appreciate that!

30:17.500 --> 30:20.367
It's Daddy O'Dewey
coming at you from
Memphis, Tennessee...

30:22.700 --> 30:25.167
Eddy Arnold,
Tennessee Plowboy.

30:25.233 --> 30:27.267
Tickets are selling out fast
so get 'em now!

30:46.767 --> 30:48.167
Hey, kid!

30:50.400 --> 30:51.533
Hey, there.

30:51.600 --> 30:52.867
Want a grape knee-high?

30:52.933 --> 30:54.900
Mighty good, ice cold.

30:54.967 --> 30:56.733
Sure, mister.

30:56.800 --> 30:59.233
Colonel, not mister.

30:59.300 --> 31:01.767
Now, look, nothin' comes
from nothing.

31:01.833 --> 31:03.567
But you know that, huh?

31:03.633 --> 31:05.433
I'm going in that
Five and Dime.

31:06.700 --> 31:08.567
By the time I come out,

31:08.633 --> 31:10.400
I don't wanna see
no other posters

31:10.467 --> 31:14.533
except Eddy Arnold
all up and down Main.

31:14.600 --> 31:15.633
You got it?

31:15.700 --> 31:17.767
What about them
Bob Wills posters?

31:18.967 --> 31:21.167
Uh, paste over 'em.

31:21.233 --> 31:22.300
Bob's a friend.

31:22.367 --> 31:23.733
He said it'd be okay.

31:25.367 --> 31:26.600
Attaboy.

31:34.800 --> 31:36.567
Eddy Arnold's coming to town!

31:37.567 --> 31:39.067
Eddy Howard?

31:39.100 --> 31:40.967
No, Eddy Arnold.

31:41.067 --> 31:43.100
Uh, Cattle Call. He's playing
two shows out at Big Dewey.
Sold out.

31:43.167 --> 31:46.833
You gonna wanna make sure
you got plenty of stock
on hand.

31:46.900 --> 31:51.067
You know what, I, I happen to
have an RCA order form
right here.

31:51.100 --> 31:52.567
50 copies ought
to keep you covered.

31:52.633 --> 31:54.700
You know what,
we better make it a 100.

31:54.767 --> 31:57.767
Uh, do you have a stamp
and an envelope?

31:57.833 --> 31:59.533
-Stamp?
-And an envelope.

32:11.900 --> 32:13.233
That's better.

32:15.067 --> 32:16.633
All right, thank you, sir.

32:16.700 --> 32:18.700
Pleasure doing
business with you.

32:18.767 --> 32:20.200
Good day.

32:34.833 --> 32:36.767
Beale Street.

32:36.833 --> 32:40.300
If we're gonna find talent
anywhere, it's here.

32:53.800 --> 32:55.267
I'm hungry. Let's go back.

32:55.333 --> 32:58.300
I'll make your favorite
bologna and Velveeta.

32:58.367 --> 33:01.167
Look, Bihari's a pretty big
player, all right?

33:01.233 --> 33:04.067
He's got two or three records
in the top 10 pretty much
every week.

33:04.067 --> 33:06.167
So you'll record
B.B. King for him.

33:06.233 --> 33:08.867
Mmm! That smells good.
I'm so hungry.

33:10.933 --> 33:12.267
There's no time for eating.

33:15.267 --> 33:17.200
See, I'm recording
this King fella?

33:17.267 --> 33:18.833
Oh, God bless Dewey
for setting it up,

33:18.900 --> 33:20.900
but that only gets us
studio time money.

33:20.967 --> 33:24.067
I gotta find me an artist
I can pitch to Bihari.

33:24.133 --> 33:25.333
My artist, not his.

33:25.400 --> 33:28.433
Now that gets us
the Do-Re-Mi Money.

33:28.500 --> 33:30.433
You're not fooling me, Sam.

33:30.500 --> 33:32.333
This is not just
about Do-Re-Mi.

33:32.400 --> 33:33.967
You're looking
for somethin' new.

33:34.067 --> 33:35.300
Different.

33:36.067 --> 33:37.267
Hear that?

33:39.100 --> 33:40.567
That band sounds hot!

33:42.500 --> 33:44.100
♪ See that girl
all dressed in blue

33:44.167 --> 33:46.333
♪ She said don't take me home
I don't mind if you do

33:46.400 --> 33:48.167
♪ 'Cause she's
doing that thing ♪

33:48.233 --> 33:52.333
Holy cow, Marion,
won't you look at that.

33:52.400 --> 33:55.067
That's a lot of music
from one man.

33:55.100 --> 33:57.700
Now don't worry,
we ain't the police
or nothing.

34:02.700 --> 34:04.633
Cheese sandwiches
look mighty good.

34:06.933 --> 34:09.133
♪ Now see that woman
with the polka dot purse

34:09.200 --> 34:11.500
♪ You're adorable, you better,
but you could do
mighty worse ♪

34:11.567 --> 34:13.100
Oh, well, we'll split one.

34:13.167 --> 34:15.767
Uh, give me one of them, uh,

34:15.833 --> 34:19.500
cheese sandwiches, a slaw,
and a potato salad, yeah?

34:24.300 --> 34:26.100
I appreciate a little
appreciation for
the BeBop Boy!

34:26.167 --> 34:27.667
Come on, now, folks, come on!

34:34.633 --> 34:35.700
Whoo-whee!

34:35.767 --> 34:39.300
Man, that was
one hell of a set.

34:39.367 --> 34:43.233
You know, walking by, I could
have swore I heard
a four-piece in here.

34:43.300 --> 34:44.800
Thank you, sir.
I'm glad you enjoyed it.

34:44.867 --> 34:47.367
-What's your name?
-Joe Hill Louis.

34:48.067 --> 34:49.233
The BeBop Boy.

34:49.300 --> 34:50.500
BeBop Boy.

34:51.267 --> 34:53.200
Sam Phillips.

34:53.267 --> 34:56.100
Now listen here,
I got a recording set-up,
corner of Union and Marshall.

34:56.167 --> 34:58.300
Now how'd you like to come by,

34:58.367 --> 35:00.767
see if we can't get somethin'
down on you?

35:00.833 --> 35:01.933
Well, sure.

35:02.067 --> 35:03.600
But can I get somethin'
to eat first?

35:03.667 --> 35:07.567
You see, my deal is I get
the kitty, sandwich and beer.

35:07.633 --> 35:08.900
You hold that thought.

35:11.967 --> 35:13.067
Sam?

35:15.767 --> 35:16.833
Eat this.

35:18.500 --> 35:22.300
BeBop Boy, we gonna make us
some records.

35:24.367 --> 35:25.733
Eat up.

35:32.100 --> 35:33.333
Order up.

35:42.700 --> 35:43.833
Hey, Trix.

35:45.433 --> 35:48.567
Hey, listen,
ain't this pretty?

35:48.633 --> 35:53.167
♪ I was dancing
with my darling

35:53.233 --> 35:57.333
♪ To the Tennessee Waltz

35:57.400 --> 35:59.400
♪ When an old friend

35:59.467 --> 36:03.433
♪ I happened to see

36:05.067 --> 36:09.500
♪ I introduced him
to my darling

36:09.567 --> 36:13.367
♪ And while they were dancing

36:13.433 --> 36:19.500
♪ My friend stole
my sweetheart from me

36:21.200 --> 36:25.100
♪ I remember the night

36:25.167 --> 36:29.333
♪ And the Tennessee Waltz

36:29.400 --> 36:31.367
♪ Now I know just

36:31.433 --> 36:35.833
♪ How much I have lost...

36:36.533 --> 36:37.633
You ruined it!

36:37.700 --> 36:39.667
You ruined everything, Elvis!

36:58.467 --> 37:00.333
Now, Mr. Phillips.

37:00.400 --> 37:02.600
The folks have been really
goin' for the Chattanoogie
Shoe Shine Boy.

37:03.500 --> 37:05.800
Well, it's been did.

37:05.867 --> 37:09.333
Tell you what,
give me somethin'
I ain't never heard.

37:09.400 --> 37:11.967
Oh, you mean a booty-shaker?

37:12.067 --> 37:14.100
Yeah, man,
give me a booty-shaker.

37:14.167 --> 37:15.733
All right.

37:15.800 --> 37:18.333
Hey, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

37:18.400 --> 37:19.767
I gotta get this down!

37:25.367 --> 37:26.700
Let's go!

37:31.767 --> 37:34.567
♪ Hey, Caldonia,

37:34.633 --> 37:36.667
♪ Now where in the world
has you been

37:36.733 --> 37:38.700
♪ Come find your soul

37:40.567 --> 37:42.433
♪ I've been here
all the afternoon ♪

37:42.500 --> 37:44.767
Marion, this is it.
By God, this is it!

37:46.533 --> 37:49.467
♪ Drinking wine
and feeling fine ♪

37:50.633 --> 37:51.867
How's that?

37:51.933 --> 37:53.767
-Yeah, man, I'm liking it.
-All right.

37:57.167 --> 37:59.433
♪ Just when I come home
from work, it's all I heard

37:59.500 --> 38:01.133
♪ These cats told me...

38:01.200 --> 38:04.167
-What is he singing about?
-It ain't about
the damn words!

